This paper is about using deep reinforcement learning for robotic manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for policy representation and off-policy training, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves visual perception for manipulation tasks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of multiple robots for parallelization, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY).
